## 

<span key="3a5ef5ce0bcb4f049770c041a814cd34"><span offset-key="3a5ef5ce0bcb4f049770c041a814cd34:0">Unlike objects, the name we give the variables doesn't matter. Let's change the above example: So, each of the variable names will ONLY count for the index-positions I fetch.</span></span>

1

<span key="1dc1a4c9c10e44e985bda516bbc7dd35"><span offset-key="1dc1a4c9c10e44e985bda516bbc7dd35:0">let arr = \['Jim', 'Bob', 'Sarah', 'Cassie'\];</span></span>

2

<span key="2925d7d2c76b475dba9d2df3249fc7f1"><span offset-key="2925d7d2c76b475dba9d2df3249fc7f1:0">let \[ var1, var2, var3, var4\] = arr;</span></span>

3

<span key="2de54c9642b040b498108187deccee21"><span offset-key="2de54c9642b040b498108187deccee21:0">console.log(var1, var2, var3, var4); //outputs: Jim Bob Sarah Cassie</span></span>

<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-h7gdob r-10ptun7 r-1vzi8xi" />

Copied!

### 

<span key="dd48cbc585f74ef282f859bb36c7904b"><span offset-key="dd48cbc585f74ef282f859bb36c7904b:0">If I include less variables then there are indexes in the arrays, then just like in Object-destructuring, only that many array element will be included in the returned array, starting from zero-index position and AGAIN without giving any meaning to the the name I give to the variables. So, each of the variable names will ONLY count for the index-positions I fetch.</span></span>

<span key="d977f3825a0a461eb7a01e00b31327b8"><span offset-key="d977f3825a0a461eb7a01e00b31327b8:0">let arr = \['Jim', 'Bob', 'Sarah', 'Cassie'\];</span></span>

<span key="0a08abd7b33e46a6bf521db90f83f1e3"><span offset-key="0a08abd7b33e46a6bf521db90f83f1e3:0">let \[ jim, bob, cassie \] = arr;</span></span>

<span key="165fc2b28fa74959a50af719bb764968"><span offset-key="165fc2b28fa74959a50af719bb764968:0">console.log(jim, bob, cassie); //outputs: Jim Bob Sarah</span></span>

<span key="1adb96516f77464bb765c3780889ec3b"><span offset-key="1adb96516f77464bb765c3780889ec3b:0">Using Spread operator - It is often used for splitting out a part of an object, but keeping the remaining properties in another object.</span></span>

<span key="c89cfc22336444d7a2f0fa2bf1ef4090"><span offset-key="c89cfc22336444d7a2f0fa2bf1ef4090:0"> hobbies: "music"</span></span>
